news.title: MahaRERA establishes counselling set up for homebuyers, developers
news.para: Both homebuyers and developers can seek guidance of these counsellors through an in-person meeting in MahaRERA’s office in Mumbai’s Bandra-Kurla Complex (BKC).

news.title: Nuvoco Vistas posts net loss of Rs 75.29 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Nuvoco Vistas' consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,608.76 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 19.68 per cent from Rs 2,179.71 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Berger Paints' manufacturing facility in Uttar Pradesh commences operations
news.para: Berger Paints has made an investment of more than Rs 1,000 crore for setting-up the manufacturing facility which has the capability to produce 15,000 KUMT per month of water-based paint, 4,800 KL per month of solvent-based paint.

news.title: SC upholds Bombay HC order protecting residents' right to form CHS
news.para: Rusabh Shah, chief promoter of New Pushpanjali Co-operative Housing Society (proposed) in Prabhadevi, had filed a petition against developer Avarsekar & Sons in 2018. Shah had challenged a rejection of the proposed society's plea to be registered as a CHS.

news.title: LIC Housing Finance's net profit dips 40% in Q3 FY23
news.para: LIC Housing Finance's consolidated total income stood at Rs 5,895.94 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 16.09 per cent from Rs 5,078.68 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Ultratech Cement commissions cement grinding unit in Odisha
news.para: This forms part of the on-going capacity expansion. With this commissioning Ultratech Cement's total cement manufacturing capacity in India now stands at 122.85 mtpa.

news.title: No impact on seven auctioned plots: Ahmedabad civic body
news.para: Senior Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) officials now say that since the valuation of the seven plots was done almost one-and-half years ago, the new jantri rates may not affect AMC’s plans to sell these plots at old rates as jantri rates are not the only factor on which base price for plots are fixed.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers posts net loss of Rs 28 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Kolte-Patil Developers' consolidated total income stood at Rs 374.46 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 52.03 per cent from Rs 244.70 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Developers to meet Gujarat CM over increase in jantri rates
news.para: CREDAI Gujarat chairman Ajay Patel said, “We have decided to meet the chief minister and we will demand that relief should be given in purchasing FSI and NA premiums to ensure projects remain viable.”

news.title: Illegal borewells found at 16 more housing projects in Gautam Buddh Nagar
news.para: The move brings an end to the borewells investigation. In the first phase, the committee, comprising the Noida district magistrate and the state and central pollution control board officials, examined 33 projects and found illegal borewells at 25 sites. In total, it has investigated 63 projects of 40 builders.

news.title: Mumbai: 25 years on, two builders get two-year rigorous imprisonment for cheating buyer
news.para: Refusing leniency to builders Harun Umatiya and Moiddiin Umatiya who have been convicted of cheating a flat buyer of Rs 4.5 lakh in 1998, metropolitan magistrate Nilesh V Bansal said the accused knew that sale deed cannot be registered unless valid permission is obtained from municipal authorities.

news.title: Bengaluru: Houses 'illegally' built below high tension power lines to be vacated
news.para: There are regulations related to building houses near KPTCL lines. It is a violation of KPTCL Act and such residents face a risk of criminal cases. We don’t give permission for construction of such houses

news.title: Nagpur civic body attaches 794 open plots for defaulting property tax
news.para: Of the 10 zones, only six — Laxmi Nagar, Dharampeth, Hanuman Nagar, Nehru Nagar, Satranjipura and Ashi Nagar — have initiated action to recover pending property tax from the owners of open plots.

news.title: Kotak Realty Fund invests over Rs 1,100 crore in The LaLiT's Bharat Hotels
news.para: The fund, a part of Kotak Mahindra Group’s alternative assets management and investment advisory business Kotak Investment Advisors, has invested in a hospitality company after more than 14 years.

news.title: EOW, Mumbai cops give clean chit to Pashmina Reality in cheating case
news.para: Ashok Mohanani, chairman of Ekta Housing, had in October last year lodged an FIR against Pashmina Realty and its directors Rajendra Singh, Kishore Koticha, Amit Jha, Preet Koticha and Rajesh Turakhia for inducing him to redevelop the prime property by presenting a rosy picture.
